# Cloudflare Pages headers for the TinyGPT playground.
#
# Cross-origin isolation enables SharedArrayBuffer, which is the precondition
# for multi-threaded WebAssembly via Worker threads. The "cross-origin isolated"
# pill on the page goes green once these headers land in production.
#
# Once SAB is available, the next perf lever (multi-thread WASM matmul) goes
# from "blocked on infrastructure" to "blocked on a WASM rebuild" — a much
# smaller box. See /roadmap lever #3.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin

# The compiled WASM module + glue need to be loadable across this isolated
# context. Public/ ships them as-is; they're our own assets so cors is fine.
/tinygpt.js
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
/tinygpt.wasm
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp

# Gallery models — 18 MB binary blobs per model. Without explicit cache
# headers Cloudflare Pages was serving them as cf-cache-status: DYNAMIC
# (i.e. ignored the edge cache entirely), so every download hit the origin.
# Now: aggressive edge caching with stale-while-revalidate so model retrains
# propagate within ~5 minutes globally without re-fetching on every click.
/gallery/*.bin
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, s-maxage=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800
/gallery/manifest.json
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=60, s-maxage=300, stale-while-revalidate=3600
